comment: I hate to say this but the reason this woman has been able to get away with so much and such a short amount of time it's simply because of our profoundly misguided take on feminism. Her timing could not have been more perfect. With you too movement and Harvey Weinstein being outed, we have people saying that if a woman claims to be abused we have to believe her. It's a ridiculous notion specially since we know that men can be abused as well. People lie. There are people of the lie and that is what this woman is. I can't understand how someone as sensitive and intelligent is Johnny Depp couldn't see through her. Frankly, I find this woman repugnant there's something about her that reeks of evil. But I shouldn't talk because I myself have my fair share of disordered assholes ruin my life. I hope that he understands that his candor about this situation and his courage in coming forward with what really happened will make it much easier for not just men to confront abuse but women as well. When I listen to him testify I was touched by how similar his reaction and feelings were about what he's been through to my own. He may be an actor but there was something very authentic and touching about his realization that he was trying to protect her after she severed his finger. I really don't like this woman. I'm a big fan of Hunter s Thompson. When I saw the film from diaries I thought the only thing wrong with it was her there's something cold and contrived about this woman and her need for attention is so extreme it's almost can't be. This is a very dangerous person. She is every bit the monster that Harvey Weinstein is and frankly Harvey Weinstein has a better excuse because he's big unyieldy and unattractive which screws people up especially in that business. I don't understand why some of these woman couldn't just give him a mercy f*** but that's the thing with the feminist. Some of them have told writers they should not have sex in their literature or writing efforts. Instead of sex they would prefer that the characters cuddle. A woman in France was discussing a rape. she said that she came to climax during the rape and the feminist went ape s***. They're so extreme and reflexive that it's almost satire listening to them talk. You can't be equal when you're making up rules that are arbitrary and inequitable. I understand that abuses an ugly thing but believe me if it wasn't Amber heard people wouldn't think much of it because it's so commonplace. The police, counselors, neighbors, do gooders, liberals you name it they have a guided attitude about abuse. I have heard educated intelligent people say that a woman deserves it because she stays. Clearly they know nothing about battered women's syndrome, cognitive dissonance, tramabonds and other unfortunate conditions that make some of us vulnerable to the disordered personalities that seem to be prolific these days. the truth is is that many people who get involved in relationships that are abusive and toxic are from difficult backgrounds where they were abused by their parents or guardian. They gravitate towards what is familiar and the abused recognize their vulnerability and the psychic scars they bear from being brought up that way. It doesn't help that people react as they do towards people who are abused and people accused of abuse because there are many women as well as men who will make up lies to protect themselves and to punish their victim. I'm glad to see this is playing out in public although I'm sure it's painful for Mr Depp. He's coming to terms with the circumstances as many people do when they discover become involved with a person who is disordered whether they're a narcissist, sociopath, or psycho. I would suggest that this woman is a sociopath because she is a sadist and she seems to derive some sort of sexual pleasure from the reactions her mistreatment provokes. I think the situation could really change our attitudes about domestic violence. I'm not sure that women are as likely to be abusive as men but I say that it's 1/3 to 2/3 which is a lot larger on the women's part than most people believe. Keep in mind there's no such thing as mutual abuse but the abuser will claim that they're abused when one has attempt it to defend themselves. I would go into the details of my own experience which was fairly recent but it's very painful to discuss and I believe that unfortunately most people are aware of exactly the pattern which Johnny Depp and I myself have suffered because we attracted the wrong people. I'm not sure if it's true or not but I do believe that I read somewhere that Johnny Depp's mother was unkind to him when he was growing up. Certainly a sensitive soul like Johnny Depp was probably bullied and experienced certain things that left a mark on him. it's funny because the people who are abused tend to be the most sensitive, honest, altruistic, and generous people around. I'm glad to count myself among them despite the scars I have physically and emotionally from abusive relationships. Godspeed Mr Depp
